Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 23:17:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.2e: Migrate 3 profile pages to useQuery
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Second slice of the T2.2 react-query fan-out. Migrates the profile
pages (TCProfilePage, PMLProfilePage, InvestorProfilePage) from
useState+useEffect+useCallback(load) to useQuery + useQueryClient.

Pattern applied (varies by page complexity):

  // Profile query — keyed by user_id
  const { data: profiles = [], isLoading } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['<Entity>Profile', { user_id: targetId }],
    queryFn: () => base44.entities.<Entity>Profile.filter({ user_id: targetId }),
    enabled: !!targetId,
  });
  const profile = profiles[0] || null;

  // Optional dependent queries (e.g. TCProfile -> Reviews)
  const { data: reviews = [] } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['Review', { tc_profile_id: profile?.id }],
    queryFn: () => base44.entities.Review.filter({ tc_profile_id: profile.id }),
    enabled: !!profile?.id,
  });

  // profileUser — currentUser shortcut or separate fetch for admin views
  const { data: profileUserList = [] } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['User', { id: targetId }],
    queryFn: () => base44.entities.User.filter({ id: targetId }),
    enabled: !isOwner && !!targetId && !!currentUser,
  });
  const profileUser = isOwner ? currentUser : (profileUserList[0] || null);

  // Invalidation replaces the load() refetch pattern
  queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['<Entity>Profile', { user_id: targetId }] });

Key improvements over T2.2a's simpler directories pattern:

- Dependent queries via 'enabled: !!profile?.id' (TCProfile -> Review)
  — react-query's natural cascade replaces manual sequencing in load()
- Three parallel queries where possible (profile, reviews, user) —
  before, they ran sequentially in load()
- Profile save now invalidates — no more manual setProfile(created) +
  load() dance
- ReviewForm onSubmitted callback uses scoped invalidation instead of
  full page reload
- Bug fix on the side: InvestorProfilePage now populates profileUser
  when admin views another user's profile. Previously name/company
  fields were blank in that case — a pre-existing gap the migration
  closes by applying the same pattern used in the other two pages.

Files (3):
- src/pages/TCProfilePage.jsx     (+31/-36)
- src/pages/PMLProfilePage.jsx    (+30/-32)
- src/pages/InvestorProfilePage.jsx (+27/-22)

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- Scoped lint: 0 errors, 1 pre-existing warning
- npm run build: succeeds
- All useEffect/useCallback eliminated from these files
- All load() calls replaced with query invalidations
